    <p class="document-paragraph">[Your Name: awdawd]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Your Address: Undefined]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Your Phone: 10000000]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Your Email: qwe@asd.com]  </p><p class="document-signature">[Date: Insert Current Date]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Mechanic&#039;s Business Name: asdasd]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">[Mechanic&#039;s Address: Undefined]  </p><p class="document-paragraph">Dear Sir/Madam,</p><p class="document-bullet">**Re: Letter of Demand for Compensation Due to Vehicle Damage**</p><p class="document-paragraph">I am writing to formally address an issue concerning damage to my vehicle, which occurred during servicing at your business on 11 April 2025. This letter serves as a Letter of Demand for compensation due to the damage incurred.</p><p class="document-bullet">**Timeline of Events:**</p><p class="document-bullet">- **Vehicle Drop-off:** On 11 April 2025, I entrusted my vehicle to your care for servicing.</p><p class="document-bullet">- **Damage Discovery:** Upon collecting my vehicle post-service, I discovered damage described as &quot;asdasdasdad.&quot;</p><p class="document-paragraph">Under the Australian Consumer Law (ACL), specifically sections concerning consumer guarantees, service providers are mandated to perform services with due care and skill. This includes taking all necessary precautions to prevent any loss or damage to the consumer&#039;s property. It is evident that the service provided by your business did not meet this standard, resulting in damage to my vehicle.</p><p class="document-signature">I am not willing to sign any release of future claims or non-disparagement agreement related to this matter. I demand full compensation for the damage caused. This compensation should cover the estimated repair costs or the insurance excess, should an insurance claim become necessary.</p><p class="document-paragraph">Please consider this letter as a formal demand for resolution. I expect a response within seven (7) days from the date of this letter. Failure to provide a satisfactory response or remedy within this timeframe will compel me to escalate the matter to Consumer Affairs Victoria and, if necessary, the Victorian Civil and Administrative Tribunal (VCAT).</p><p class="document-paragraph">I trust this matter can be resolved promptly and professionally. I look forward to your immediate attention to this issue.</p><p class="document-paragraph">Yours sincerely,</p><p class="document-signature">[Signature]</p><p class="document-paragraph">awdawd</p><p class="document-bullet">---</p><p class="document-paragraph">Please ensure that all undefined fields (such as your address, the mechanic&#039;s address, and any other missing details) are filled in before sending this letter. This document aims to protect your rights under the Australian Consumer Law and seek a fair resolution to the damage caused.</p>
    
